Square $EFGH$ in the coordinate plane has vertices at the points $E(2,2), F(-2,2), G(-2,-2), H(2,-2)$. Consider these transformations:
- $L$, a rotation of $90^{\circ}$ counterclockwise around the origin;
- $R$, a rotation of $90^{\circ}$ clockwise around the origin;
- $H$, a reflection across the $x$-axis;
- $V$, a reflection across the $y$-axis;
- $S$, a scaling by a factor of 2 centered at the origin.
How many sequences of $24$ transformations chosen from $\{L, R, H, V, S\}$ will send all of the labeled vertices back to their original positions?
A) $286$
B) $300$
C) $400$
D) $455$
E) $500$

